---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base.astro";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
import SimpleSyphilisChart from "@/components/charts/SimpleSyphilisChart.astro";
---

<PageLayout meta={{ title: "Home" }}>
	<!-- Streamlined Hero Section with Gradient Background -->
	<section class="hero-section relative -mx-8 mb-10 overflow-hidden px-8 py-10 dark:bg-gray-900">
		<div
			class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-700 to-blue-900 opacity-90 dark:opacity-70"
		>
		</div>
		<div class="bg-pattern absolute inset-0 opacity-10"></div>

		<!-- Visual elements that suggest data/research -->
		<div
			class="absolute top-0 right-0 h-1 w-full bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-blue-400 to-transparent opacity-50"
		>
		</div>
		<div
			class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 h-1 w-full bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-400 via-transparent to-blue-400 opacity-30"
		>
		</div>

		<!-- Subtle Background Elements -->
		<div class="absolute top-6 right-8 h-24 w-24 rounded-full bg-white opacity-5"></div>
		<div class="absolute bottom-6 left-8 h-16 w-16 rounded-full bg-white opacity-5"></div>

		<div class="hero-content relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-5xl">
			<div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-6 md:flex-row md:justify-between">
				<!-- Left side: Logo and Title -->
				<div class="flex flex-col items-center text-center md:w-1/2 md:items-start md:text-left">
					<div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-4">
						<div
							class="ring-opacity-30 h-14 w-14 rounded-lg bg-white p-2 ring-2 shadow-md ring-blue-500 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:ring-blue-400"
						>
							<svg
								viewBox="0 0 200 200"
								fill="none"
								xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
								class="h-full w-full text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400"
							>
								<path
									d="M100 10 L180 40 L180 90 C180 130 150 170 100 190 C50 170 20 130 20 90 L20 40 L100 10Z"
									fill="currentColor"
									stroke="#fff"
									stroke-width="5"
									class="dark:stroke-gray-700"></path>
								<path
									d="M100 30 L160 55 L160 90 C160 120 135 150 100 165 C65 150 40 120 40 90 L40 55 L100 30Z"
									fill="#fff"
									stroke="none"
									class="dark:fill-gray-700"></path>
								<path
									d="M80 80 L90 70 L120 100 L90 130 L80 120 L100 100 L80 80Z"
									fill="currentColor"
									stroke="none"></path>
							</svg>
						</div>
						<h1
							class="fade-in text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl"
						>
							<span class="text-shadow">SHIELD <span class="text-blue-200">Project</span></span>
						</h1>
					</div>

					<div
						class="slide-in border-opacity-30 mb-4 max-w-md border-b border-blue-400 pb-2 text-lg font-light text-blue-100 md:text-xl"
					>
						<p>Syphilis and HIV Integrated Epidemiologic and Economic Local-level Dynamics</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Right side: Description and Buttons -->
				<div class="md:w-1/2">
					<div class="slide-in mb-5" style="animation-delay: 0.1s;">
						<p
							class="rounded-lg border-l-2 border-blue-300 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-700 to-blue-800 p-3 text-lg text-white shadow-sm"
						>
							Developing evidence-based modeling to address the rising syphilis epidemic in the US
							and its intersection with HIV.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="slide-in flex flex-wrap gap-4" style="animation-delay: 0.15s;">
						<a
							href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/about`}
							class="btn bg-white text-blue-700 transition-all hover:bg-blue-50 hover:shadow-md"
						>
							Learn More
						</a>
						<a
							href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/research`}
							class="btn btn-outline border-white text-white hover:bg-blue-900/20 hover:text-white"
						>
							Research Methods
						</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Team-provided Project Description -->
	<section class="my-16">
		<div class="card dark:border-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-900">
			<p class="mb-4 dark:text-gray-300">
				Syphilis rates in the United States (US) have reached their highest levels in decades,
				doubling in the past five years alone. The US syphilis epidemic is tied to HIV, with 25-50%
				of syphilis infections occurring among people with HIV (PWH). Both syphilis and HIV
				disproportionately affect racial, ethnic, and sexual minorities.
			</p>
			<p class="mb-4 dark:text-gray-300">
				Despite the historical effectiveness of traditional methods, modern syphilis control in the
				US faces challenges due to the erosion of national infrastructure for combating sexually
				transmitted infections and the continued decline in public health budgets. This raises the
				question:
				<strong
					>"What are the most efficient and cost-effective strategies for investing in tools such as
					testing, partner services, and preventive counseling to curb the US syphilis epidemic?"</strong
				>
			</p>

			<!-- CDC graph in a simpler presentation -->
			<div class="my-8 flex justify-center">
				<SimpleSyphilisChart />
			</div>

			<p class="mb-4 dark:text-gray-300">
				New innovative strategies, such as doxycycline for post-exposure prophylaxis ("doxy-PEP")
				and diagnostics like point-of-care (POC) or at-home testing, offer promise in reducing
				syphilis incidence. However, disparities in interventions' uptake can exacerbate existing
				racial and ethnic disparities in health outcomes. Thus, the question arises:
				<strong
					>"What are the most effective strategies for targeting emerging interventions at various
					subgroups, and what conditions would render these strategies both cost-effective and
					equitable?"</strong
				>
			</p>
			<p class="dark:text-gray-300">
				Supported by a 5-year grant from the National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases
				(NIAID) [R01AI179776 PI: Kasaie], this study addresses a significant gap in representative
				models for the US syphilis and HIV epidemic by introducing a novel suite of <strong
					>S</strong
				>yphilis and
				<strong>H</strong>IV <strong>I</strong>ntegrated <strong>E</strong>pidemiologic and Economic <strong
					>L</strong
				>ocal-level
				<strong>D</strong>ynamics (SHIELD) models. These models will cover 32 US cities containing
				all Ending the HIV Epidemic (EHE) urban jurisdictions, comprising 60% of both syphilis and
				HIV diagnoses.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Research Aims with Improved Card Design -->
	<section class="my-16">
		<h2 class="section-heading text-center dark:text-blue-300">Research Aims</h2>

		<div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-3">
			<div
				class="card p-5 hover:border-blue-200 dark:border-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-900 dark:hover:border-blue-700"
			>
				<div class="mb-5 text-blue-500 dark:text-blue-400">
					<Icon name="mdi:magnify-expand" class="h-10 w-10" />
				</div>
				<h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-bold dark:text-white">Aim 1: Existing Control Strategies</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
					Assessing the impact and cost-effectiveness of expanding existing syphilis control
					strategies to reduce the burden and racial ethnic disparities in syphilis incidence, among
					PWH and the general population.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div
				class="card p-5 hover:border-blue-200 dark:border-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-900 dark:hover:border-blue-700"
			>
				<div class="mb-5 text-blue-500 dark:text-blue-400">
					<Icon name="mdi:chart-bell-curve" class="h-10 w-10" />
				</div>
				<h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-bold dark:text-white">Aim 2: Emerging Strategies</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
					Projecting the impact of emerging strategies on syphilis burden and disparities, and
					identifying the conditions under which these strategies would be cost-effective and
					equitable.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div
				class="card p-5 hover:border-blue-200 dark:border-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-900 dark:hover:border-blue-700"
			>
				<div class="mb-5 text-blue-500 dark:text-blue-400">
					<Icon name="mdi:tools" class="h-10 w-10" />
				</div>
				<h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-bold dark:text-white">Aim 3: Decision Support Toolkit</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
					Developing a policy support toolkit and framework for tailoring localized, cost-effective,
					equitable strategies to reduce syphilis among PWH and the general population.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="my-16">
		<div class="card bg-blue-600 p-6 text-center text-white dark:bg-blue-800">
			<h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">Our Impact</h2>
			<p class="mx-auto mb-6 max-w-xl">
				Our findings will provide actionable insights and tools to support decision-makers in
				crafting effective responses to the syphilis and HIV epidemic, tailored to the specific
				needs and characteristics of their communities.
			</p>
			<div class="flex justify-center">
				<a
					href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/team`}
					class="inline-block rounded-lg bg-white px-6 py-3 font-medium text-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-200 dark:text-blue-800 dark:hover:bg-blue-100"
					>Meet Our Team</a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</PageLayout>

<style>
	.hero-section {
		background-color: #1e429f;
	}

	.bg-pattern {
		background-image: url("data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg width='60' height='60' viewBox='0 0 60 60' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cg fill='none' fill-rule='evenodd'%3E%3Cg fill='%23ffffff' fill-opacity='0.1'%3E%3Cpath d='M36 34v-4h-2v4h-4v2h4v4h2v-4h4v-2h-4zm0-30V0h-2v4h-4v2h4v4h2V6h4V4h-4zM6 34v-4H4v4H0v2h4v4h2v-4h4v-2H6zM6 4V0H4v4H0v2h4v4h2V6h4V4H6z'/%3E%3C/g%3E%3C/g%3E%3C/svg%3E");
	}

	.text-shadow {
		text-shadow: 0 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
	}

	@keyframes float {
		0% {
			transform: translateY(0px);
		}
		50% {
			transform: translateY(-3px);
		}
		100% {
			transform: translateY(0px);
		}
	}

	.hero-content {
		animation: float 6s ease-in-out infinite;
	}

	.fade-in {
		animation: fadeIn 1s ease-out forwards;
	}

	.slide-in {
		opacity: 0;
		animation: slideIn 0.9s ease-out forwards;
	}

	@keyframes fadeIn {
		from {
			opacity: 0;
		}
		to {
			opacity: 1;
		}
	}

	@keyframes slideIn {
		from {
			opacity: 0;
			transform: translateY(5px);
		}
		to {
			opacity: 1;
			transform: translateY(0);
		}
	}
</style>
